        <h2>Why Test Your <%= country %> Proxy or VPN?</h2>
        <p>
            Simply having a VPN or proxy that claims to route your traffic through <%= country %> is not enough. 
            Many VPN providers and proxy services have critical leaks that silently expose your real identity — even when the connection appears active. 
            The most common and dangerous of these are <strong>WebRTC leaks</strong>, <strong>DNS leaks</strong>, and <strong>timezone mismatches</strong>.
        </p>
        <p>
            A WebRTC leak exposes your real IP address directly from your browser, bypassing your <%= country %> proxy tunnel entirely. 
            A DNS leak means your DNS queries are being sent to your original ISP instead of routing through your proxy, 
            revealing every domain you visit. And a timezone mismatch — where your browser clock says one region but your IP says <%= country %> — 
            is an instant red flag for any website using browser fingerprinting.
        </p>
        <p>
            <a href="/">Whoer Live</a> tests for all of these automatically, showing you exactly what websites and ad trackers can see about your connection — in real time.
        </p>

